                    text: '<strong>The ideal</strong>: Children have complete autonomy + zero predators.\n\n<strong>The reality</strong>: Predators exist + children vulnerable.\n\n<strong>Therefore</strong>: Must balance autonomy and protection.\n\n---\n\n<strong>The balance we chose</strong>:\n\n<strong>Maximum autonomy compatible with safety</strong>:\n- Child CAN exit (not trapped)\n- Child CAN choose (between safe alternatives)\n- Child CANNOT be lured by predators (alternatives vetted)\n- Child\'s autonomy grows (as cognitive capacity increases)\n\n---\n\n<strong>As world improves</strong> (predators neutralized through MWR 4 + Trust Networks):\n\n<strong>Stage 1</strong> (current): Heavy vetting required (predator risk high) → restricted exit options\n\n<strong>Stage 2</strong> (predators partially reduced): Moderate vetting (predator risk moderate) → more exit options\n\n<strong>Stage 3</strong> (predators mostly eliminated): Light vetting (predator risk low) → broad exit options\n\n<strong>Stage 4</strong> (ideal world achieved): Minimal vetting (predator risk near-zero) → children approach unrestricted exit\n\n---\n\n<strong>We\'re in Stage 1</strong> (must protect heavily).\n\n<strong>Working toward Stage 4</strong> (where children can truly be free).\n\n<strong>Until then</strong>: Freedom within protection (best balance we can achieve given predator reality).'
